    <note>Sun(1) Zhi [17907] According to Wang(2) Yucheng's [3997] inscription for descendant, Yong(2) [17912] (q.v.), his ancestors served under the Three Kingdom's state of Wu and Zhi was the first to cross the river (in one of the few cases of a move from south to north), where his son settled in Cai--I assume after burying his father, Zhi, who served in the area. Suzhou may not be the ancestral home since Wu covers a large area. But these must be Wujun Sun(1).</note>
